title: What Does Grilling Mean

transcripts:
[MUSIC PLAYING]
Grilling is cooking meat over direct heat on clean dry grates that are about to 350 to 450 degrees Fahrenheit. Today we're cooking on a Char-Broil Infrared grill that has a wide range of cooking temperatures. You'll find these settings are perfect for seasoned or marinated meat like these beautiful pork chops or chicken thighs. Oh don't those look tasty.
